comment: There is a natural one-to-one mapping from ` ( RR X. RR ) ` to ` CC ` , where we map ` <. x , y >. ` to ` ( x + ( _i x. y ) ) ` . In our construction of the complex numbers, this is in fact our _definition_ of ` CC ` (see ~ df-c ), but in the axiomatic treatment we can only show that there is the expected mapping between these two sets. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 16-Jun-2013.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 17-Feb-2014.)
